This makes for an interesting issue for [AMBARI-22852](https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/AMBARI-22852) that was not initially considered.  There is an effort to allow a user to change the cluster's Zookeeper principal name when Kerberos is enabled. However, if Infra Solr can be configured to use an external Zookeeper then maybe it also needs to know whether that Zookeeper has Kerberos enabled; and if so, what the relevant principal name is. 

CC: @smolnar82
@rlevas , yes that would mean we will need an external zookeeper principal and keytab to infra solr, so probably that should be included in this patch as well (same has been done for logsearch)
asking re-review @rlevas @smolnar82
